 <fr:p>This follows in essentially the same way as <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00BH.xml"
addr="jms-00BH"
title="Sections need not be embeddings">sections need not be embeddings</fr:link>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {K}]]></fr:tex> be <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {Cat}]]></fr:tex> and consider the circle <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S^1]]></fr:tex> viewed as the free groupoid generated by a point and a loop. Then the base point <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {1}\xrightarrow {\mathsf {base}} S^1]]></fr:tex> is not fully faithful, as there are <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Z}]]></fr:tex> many endomorphisms on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {base}]]></fr:tex> that do not lie in the image of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {1}\xrightarrow {\mathsf {base}} S^1]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
